  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Human Resource Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong>:</p><ul><li><p>Assist in the full spectrum of HR functions, excluding payroll.</p></li><li><p>Participate in the staff recruitment process, including job postings, resume screening, phone screening, and interview coordination with hiring managers.</p></li><li><p>Efficiently utilize various recruitment platforms, participate in recruitment job fairs, and proactively support internship programs.</p></li><li><p>Monitor staff attendance records on a weekly basis and update department heads regarding attendance issues such as lateness, absences, or missing clock-in/clock-out records.</p></li><li><p>Assist in drafting and implementing HR policies, including but not limited to prepare HR memo and updating the employee handbook.</p></li><li><p>Manage employee engagement matters, including on-boarding and off-boarding processes, workplace safety issues, employee grievances, and disciplinary actions in a timely manner.</p></li><li><p>Prepare HR-related letters such as appointment letters, confirmation letters, warning letters, and other relevant documents.</p></li><li><p>Serve as a backup for worker dormitory administration, including check-in registration and de-registration for dormitory exit.</p></li><li><p>Ensure proper documentation and record-keeping of issues raised by staff, and follow up promptly to facilitate timely resolution.</p></li><li><p>Serve as a backup in facilitating course registrations for employees, such as safety courses and other work-related training approved by department heads.</p></li><li><p>Assist in organizing company events, including Christmas celebrations, annual dinners, and other employee activities.</p></li><li><p>Assist in foreign worker work pass matters, including new applications, renewals, cancellations, and coordination of medical check-ups.</p></li><li><p>Perform any other duties assigned by the Management. <br /><br /><br /><strong>Job Requirements: </strong><br /><br />Minimum 5 years of hands-on HR experience, preferably in logistic or construction sector.</p><p><p>Strong knowledge of Singapore Employment Act.</p></p><p><p>Excellent interpersonal and communication skills with different levels of stakeholders.</p></p><p><p>Ability to multi-task, stay organized, and work independently in a fast-paced environment.</p></p><p><p>Proficient in MS Office and HR systems.</p></p></li></ul>",
